*--------------------SUDO--------------------*

    sudo("superuser do", or "switch user do") allows a user with properpermissionsto execute a command as another user, such as thesuperuser.
    sudoallows a permitted user to execute a command as another user, according to specifications in the/etc/sudoersfile.
    

*--------------------how to provide SUDO Privilege--------------------*

    For edit configuration file:
        # vim /etc/sudoers
        root ALL=(ALL)   ALL
        amir ALL=(ALL)   ALL (add this line appro. 101 line)
        
    :wq
    
    eg:
        #su amir
        amir$sudo useradd salman
